page.title: 06Types of houses in Lavant
page.content: There is a mixture of old and new houses in this area.There are three thatched houses in Lavant,one in East Lavant,and there are two in Mid Lavant.There is one by the allotments and another by the Royal Oak.There are two white houses by Yarbrooke and they are about 50 years old.There are some flint Houses in East Lavant and in Mid Lavant.There are eight roughcast houses called Parkers cottages in East Lavant by Chalkpit Lane. There are new brick houses behind St.Nicholas Road,they have been there for 7 months and the others are 1 year old.The houses that people live in St.Nicholas Rd.are 21 years old.There are still some houses belonging to Goodwood.The old school is 130 years old.
